    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Lecture 1.1 Root Finding Methods: Searching Method\"\ndescription: \"Searching Method\"\ndate: 2025-03-28\ncategories: [numerical-analysis, python]\nimage: bolzanos_theorem.png\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nSearching method is used to locate intervals where a root is hidden before using more precise methods like Bisection or Newton-Raphson.\n\n**Important idea**: We are looking for a sign change in the function. If $f(x)$ goes from negative to positive (or vice versa), the curve must have crossed the x-axis.\n\n## Theoretical Basis\n\nWe are going to support our analysis in Bolzano's theorem:\n\nLet $f$ be a continuous function on a closed interval $[a, b]$. If $f(a) \\cdot f(b) < 0$, then:\n\n$$\\exists \\, c \\in (a, b) \\text{ such that } f(c) = 0$$\n\nThis theorem is so powerful because it guarantees that there's at least one root in $[a, b]$.\n\n## The algorithm\n\nLet be i the iteration, if a sequence of points is defined as follows:\n\n$$x_{i+1} = x_i + \\Delta x $$\n\nWe can evaluate the crossing condition at each step:\n\n$$f(x_i) \\cdot f(x_{i+1}) < 0$$\n\nIf this is true, the root is in the interval:\n\n$$(x_i, x_{i+1})$$\n\nIf not, $f>0$, we continue \"walking\" $\\Delta x$\n\n## The error\n\nIn Incremental Search, we do not obtain the exact value of the root, but rather a confidence interval. If we find a sign change between $x_i$ and $x_{i+1}$, the maximum possible error (the maximum distance to the real root) is the step size:\n\n$$E_{max} \\approx \\Delta x$$\n\n## Hands on\n\nThis code is made for applying the searching algorithm to find the roots in quadratic equations, the idea is to show the diference between the analytic solution and the aproximation interval. It is important to mention that this is a modified version. Not only do it works for positive intervals but also for negative ones.\n\n::: {#caf9e42d .cell execution_count=1}\n``` {.python .cell-code code-fold=\"true\" code-summary=\"See implementation\"}\nimport pandas as pd\n\n# Parameters\na = 1.0\nb = -3.0\nc = 2.0\ndeltax = 0.1\n\ndef searching(roots, step):\n  intervalos = []\n  historial = []\n  x = 0.0\n  iterations = 0\n  flag = 0\n  while flag != roots:\n    cuadraticfuncion = lambda a1, b1, c1, x1 : a1*pow(x1, 2) + b1*x1 + c1\n    cuadraticfuncionn = lambda a1, b1, c1, x1 : a1*pow(-x1, 2) + b1*(-x1) + c1\n    fi_p = cuadraticfuncion(a, b, c, x)\n    fi_n = cuadraticfuncionn(a, b, c, x)\n    x = x + step\n    fi_1_p = cuadraticfuncion(a, b, c, x)\n    fi_1_n = cuadraticfuncionn(a, b, c, x)\n    if bool(fi_p<0):\n      f1 = -1\n    else:\n      f1 = 1\n    if bool(fi_1_p<0):\n      f2 = -1\n    else:\n      f2 = 1\n    if bool(fi_n<0):\n      f3 = -1\n    else:\n      f3 = 1\n    if bool(fi_1_n<0):\n      f4 = -1\n    else:\n      f4 = 1\n    if f1*f2 < 0:\n      flag += 1\n      xi_1p = x\n      xip = x - step\n      intervalos.append([xip, xi_1p])\n      historial.append({\"Iterations\": iterations, \"xi\": round(xip,4), \"xi+1\": round(xi_1p,4), \"f(xi)\": round(fi_p,4), \"f(xi+1)\": round(fi_1_p,4), \"Raíz\": \"Found in Positive side\"})\n    else:\n      xi_1p = x\n      xip = x - step\n      historial.append({\"Iterations\": iterations, \"xi\": round(xip,4), \"xi+1\": round(xi_1p,4), \"f(xi)\": round(fi_p,4), \"f(xi+1)\": round(fi_1_p,4), \"Raíz\": \"Not found\"})\n    if f3*f4 < 0:\n      flag += 1\n      xi_1n = -1 * x\n      xin = xi_1n + step\n      intervalos.append([xin, xi_1n])\n      historial.append({\"Iterations\": iterations, \"xi\": round(xin,4), \"xi+1\": round(xi_1n,4), \"f(xi)\": round(fi_n,4), \"f(xi+1)\": round(fi_1_n,4), \"Raíz\": \"Found in Negative side\"})\n    else:\n      xi_1n = -1 * x\n      xin = xi_1n + step\n      historial.append({\"Iterations\": iterations, \"xi\": round(xin,4), \"xi+1\": round(xi_1n,4), \"f(xi)\": round(fi_n,4), \"f(xi+1)\": round(fi_1_n,4), \"Raíz\": \"Not found\"})\n    \n    iterations += 1\n\n  print(\"¡Great! We have found all roots!\")\n  print(\"Intervals:\", intervalos)\n  return historial\n\n# Execution\nprint(f\"f(x) = {a}x² + {b}x + {c}\")\ndiscriminant = pow(b,2) - (4*a*c)\nprint(f\"Discriminant: {discriminant}\")\n\nif discriminant < 0:\n    print(\"There aren't real roots\")\nelif discriminant == 0:\n    historial = searching(1, deltax)\nelse:\n    historial = searching(2, deltax)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n```\nf(x) = 1.0x² + -3.0x + 2.0\nDiscriminant: 1.0\n¡Great! We have found all roots!\nIntervals: [[0.9999999999999999, 1.0999999999999999], [1.9000000000000004, 2.0000000000000004]]\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Iterations\n\n::: {#c71c3b4f .cell execution_count=2}\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=2}\n```{=html}\n<div>\n<style scoped>\n    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n        vertical-align: middle;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n        vertical-align: top;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe thead th {\n        text-align: right;\n    }\n</style>\n<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n      <th></th>\n      <th>Iterations</th>\n      <th>xi</th>\n      <th>xi+1</th>\n      <th>f(xi)</th>\n      <th>f(xi+1)</th>\n      <th>Raíz</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th>0</th>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>0.0</td>\n      <td>0.1</td>\n      <td>2.00</td>\n      <td>1.71</td>\n      <td>Not found</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>1</th>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>0.0</td>\n      <td>-0.1</td>\n      <td>2.00</td>\n      <td>2.31</td>\n      <td>Not found</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>2</th>\n      <td>1</td>\n      <td>0.1</td>\n      <td>0.2</td>\n      <td>1.71</td>\n      <td>1.44</td>\n      <td>Not found</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>3</th>\n      <td>1</td>\n      <td>-0.1</td>\n      <td>-0.2</td>\n      <td>2.31</td>\n      <td>2.64</td>\n      <td>Not found</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>4</th>\n      <td>2</td>\n      <td>0.2</td>\n      <td>0.3</td>\n      <